Below is a summary of what the GPL means for ISPH users:

(1) Anyone is free to use, modify, or extend ISPH in 
any way they choose, including for commercial purposes.

(2) If you distribute a modified version of ISPH, it 
must remain open-source, meaning you distribute it under 
the terms of the GPL. You should clearly annotate such 
a code as a derivative version of ISPH.

(3) If you release any code that includes ISPH source 
code, then it must also be open-sourced, meaning you 
distribute it under the terms of the GPL.

(4) If you give ISPH files to someone else, the GPL 
LICENSE file and source file headers (including the
copyright and GPL notices) should remain part of the code.